83rd OREGON LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY--2026 Regular Session
House Bill 4013
Introduced and printed pursuant to House Rule 12.00. Presession filed (at the request of House Interim Committee
on Labor and Workforce Development for Representative Dacia Grayber)
SUMMARY
The following summary is not prepared by the sponsors of the measure and is not a part of the body thereof subject
to consideration by the Legislative Assembly. It is an editor’s brief statement of the essential features of the
measure as introduced. The statement includes a measure digest written in compliance with applicable readability
standards.
Digest: The Act specifies which federal rules BOLI must use when adopting rules that set work
hour limits for minors. (Flesch Readability Score: 62.8).
Clarifies which federal rules apply to the scope of the rulemaking authority of the Bureau of
Labor and Industries regarding rules that govern the hours a minor can work.
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT
2 Relating to labor standards; amending ORS 653.307.
3 Be It Enacted by the People of the State of Oregon:
4 SECTION 1. ORS 653.307 is amended to read:
5 653.307. (1) In accordance with the applicable provisions of ORS chapter 183, the Bureau of
6 Labor and Industries shall adopt rules governing annual employment certificates required under this
7 section. After September 9, 1995, the rules governing the total hours a minor can work may not be
8 [more] less restrictive than the requirements of the federal Fair Labor Standards Act (29 U.S.C. 201,
9 et seq.), [unless otherwise provided by Oregon law] as in effect on January 1, 2026, but may be
10 more restrictive only as necessary to implement or conform to changes in the federal Act
11 or state law that increase protections for minors.
12 (2) An employer who hires minors shall apply to the bureau for an annual employment certif-
13 icate to employ minors. The application shall be on a form provided by the bureau and shall include,
14 but need not be limited to:
15 (a) The estimated or average number of minors to be employed during the year.
16 (b) A description of the activities to be performed.
17 (c) A description of the machinery or other equipment to be used by the minors.
18 (3) Once a year, the bureau shall provide to all employers applying for an annual employment
19 certificate an information sheet summarizing all rules and laws governing the employment of minors.
20 (4) Failure by an employer to comply with ORS 653.305 to 653.340 or with the regulations
21 adopted by the bureau pursuant to this section shall subject the employer to revocation of the right
22 to hire minors in the future at the discretion of the bureau, provided that an employer shall be
23 granted a hearing before the bureau prior to such action being taken.
24 (5) All school districts shall cooperate with the bureau and make available, upon request of the
25 bureau, information concerning the age and schooling of minors.
26
NOTE: Matter in boldfaced type in an amended section is new; matter [italic and bracketed] is existing law to be omitted.
New sections are in boldfaced type.
